1: # Implementation Guidance
2: 
3: ## Overview
4: 
5: This section provides technical details for developers implementing the Custom Tools specification, covering key implementation considerations and best practices.
6: 
7: ## Parameter Substitution and Escaping
8: 
9: ### Parameter Replacement
10: 
11: Parameters in commands are enclosed in curly braces (`{PARAM_NAME}`) and should be replaced with the actual parameter values before execution. The implementation should:
12: 
13: 1. Find all parameters in the command template
14: 2. Replace each parameter with its value
15: 3. Apply appropriate transformations and formats
16: 4. Handle escape sequences properly
17: 
18: Example implementation:
19: ```csharp
20: private string SubstituteParameters(string command, Dictionary<string, object> parameters)
21: {
22:     foreach (var param in parameters)
23:     {
24:         var placeholder = $"{{{param.Key}}}";
25:         var value = param.Value?.ToString() ?? string.Empty;
26:         
27:         // Apply transformations if defined
28:         if (parameterDefinitions.TryGetValue(param.Key, out var definition) && 
29:             !string.IsNullOrEmpty(definition.Transform))
30:         {
31:             value = ApplyTransformation(value, definition.Transform);
32:         }
33:         
34:         // Format the parameter if specified
35:         if (definition?.Format != null)
36:         {
37:             value = definition.Format.Replace("{value}", value);
38:         }
39:         
40:         // Escape shell metacharacters if required
41:         if (definition?.Security?.EscapeShell == true)
42:         {
43:             value = EscapeShellArgument(value);
44:         }
45:         
46:         command = command.Replace(placeholder, value);
47:     }
48:     
49:     return command;
50: }
